  "translations": {
    "en": "Secondly, I exhort you to adopt the ways of Taqwa, to be mindful of your duties by guarding against all sins and evils, in all matters for which you are answerable to Him, for unto Him is your return. Surely, Allah, Most High, says: 'Every soul is a hostage to what it has earned' [74:38], and He says: 'Allah warns you to beware of Him, and unto Him is the ultimate return' [3:28]. And He says: 'By your Lord, We shall question them all, regarding what they used to do' [15:92-93].",
    "ur": "Secondly, I exhort you to adopt the ways of Taqwa, to be mindful of your duties by guarding against all sins and evils, in all matters for which you are answerable to Him, for unto Him is your return. Surely, Allah, Most High, says: 'Every soul is a hostage to what it has earned' [74:38], and He says: 'Allah warns you to beware of Him, and unto Him is the ultimate return' [3:28]. And He says: 'By your Lord, We shall question them all, regarding what they used to do' [15:92-93].",
